# Raw-functional-interface reassignment cast (JDEC_LAMBDA_ASSIGN_CAST_OFF): the local is declared RAW
# `Function var2 = this.builder;` (raw field, no Signature), so a method reference / explicitly-typed
# lambda REASSIGNED into it must be cast to a parameterized `Function<...>` to bind against the raw SAM,
# exactly as the javac-visible source does. A bare `var2 = Collections::unmodifiableCollection;` is an
# "invalid method reference" and a bare `var2 = (Collection l0) -> ...` has "incompatible parameter
# types in lambda expression". Real hit: fastjson2 ObjectReaderImplList.
+(Function<Collection, Collection>)(Collections::unmodifiableCollection)
+(Function<Collection, Collection>)((Collection l0) ->
-/=\s*Collections::unmodifiableCollection;/
